org.gvsig.fmap.dal.coverage.filter

Interface FilterLoader

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    FilterLoaderImpl

    public interface FilterLoader

    Applies the stack of filters to a buffer. With the same FilterLoader you can process different buffers. Each buffer can use a different environment

      • getTransparency

        Transparency getTransparency()
        Gets the transparency object and the color interpretation of the result. Mostly, filters returns ARGB images but sometimes the filter can modify the transparency configuration and the color interpretation. For instance, when a color table is applied or a alpha band is added by the filter.
        Returns:

      • getBufferResult

        Buffer getBufferResult()
        Gets the buffer result after the function applyFilters is executed. If the buffer has not been modified, it will return the input buffer.
        Returns:
